<h1>Tufting Europe | Curated Supplies for Tufting & Rug Makers</h1>
<p>&nbsp;Tufting Europe is a premium supplier dedicated to artists and rug makers, offering high-quality tufting machines and carefully curated supplies. The company focuses on trusted quality, fast shipping, and reliable European warranty, ensuring customers receive both excellent products and dependable support. Since 2019, Tufting Europe has aimed to make the art of tufting accessible to everyone by combining affordable pricing with strong customer service and efficient delivery throughout Europe.</p>
<div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><a href="https://tuftingeurope.com/"><img border="0" src="https://blogger.googleusercontent.com/img/b/R29vZ2xl/AVvXsEj3V08jjiSse6UTCTg7_AxnCmVo_Ni77s7vZuP_LRiaPGx00_yfJvFbcR7a2OyapdHHNg41rdYlpsHU7NXPUBe742lREJVEkP0A3KIPu7i2Vl9Ze5WDLdRxqQ4TVFz9Kt-LDTNK_dWhyphenhyphena7KhDupkt1zU74fpJwb1hup0_lYOlIikGhshujHqLCoB-IH6hyphenhyphenz/s780/1_6HMDzhaNNrOkgIqW1cjsSg.png" /></a></div>
<p>&nbsp;The webshop provides everything needed for tufting, including yarn, tufting guns, tufting cloth, starter kits, accessories, frames, and grips. Customers can easily find essential tools and materials to set up their own creative workspace at home. In addition to physical products, Tufting Europe also offers an online tufting course designed to help beginners and experienced makers turn their ideas into finished rugs. The course shares practical knowledge gathered over years of experience and includes coaching to help improve skills more quickly. Interested participants can join a waitlist to gain early access and benefit from a special launch discount.</p>
<p>&nbsp;Getting started with tufting is presented as a simple three-step process. First, customers order a reliable and authentic tufting machine to ensure a smooth and safe experience. Second, they build a home studio by preparing a sturdy frame, attaching tufting cloth, and selecting yarn. Proper preparation is emphasized as an important foundation for successful projects. Third, they begin creating rugs, exploring endless design possibilities ranging from minimalistic styles to bold and psychedelic patterns.</p>
<p>&nbsp;One of the flagship products is the AK-V Tufting Gun, priced at €220.00 and highly rated by customers. Designed for precision, comfort, and ease of use, the AK-V operates smoothly and quietly. It features a real-time speed display, a front LED light for better visibility, and an improved cutting mechanism compared to earlier models. Released in a new purple edition on 26 November 2025, this machine supports both cut and loop pile styles, allowing users to switch by deactivating the scissors. The pile height is adjustable between 8 and 16 mm, and the speed can be controlled with an adjustable dial. The machine runs on 100–240V with an EU plug and weighs 1.4 kg. Each package includes the tufting gun, a power brick with EU plug, and spare parts for maintenance. Users are advised to familiarize themselves with the machine before adjusting pile height, as improper changes may affect performance and void the warranty. Safety guidelines stress unplugging the machine before adjustments, keeping it out of children’s reach, and handling it responsibly. The AK-V comes with a two-year warranty and customer support, reinforcing the company’s commitment to quality and authenticity.</p>
<p>&nbsp;Tufting Europe offers several starter kits designed to help beginners begin confidently. The Ultimate Tufting Starter Kit with AK-V and Frame, currently discounted from €469.00 to €439.00, includes everything required to create professional rugs at home. The kit contains the new AK-V tufting machine with speed display and LED light, a sturdy 90x90 cm tabletop tufting frame with clamps and cloth gripper strips, 200x200 cm of primary tufting cloth, and 200x200 cm of anti-slip backing. It also includes accessories such as rug shaving and carving clippers, an adjustable shaving guide, duckbill napping shears, sewing machine oil, a flexible latex spatula, and a loop threader. Customers only need to purchase yarn in their preferred colors and latex carpet glue separately. The kit is delivered in two boxes, one containing the frame and the other the remaining materials.</p>
<p>&nbsp;Another option is the Tufting Starter Kit with AK-V, discounted from €369.00 to €349.00. This kit includes the AK-V machine, 200x200 cm of primary tufting cloth, anti-slip backing, rug shaving and carving clippers, an adjustable shaving guide, duckbill napping shears, sewing machine oil, and a flexible latex spatula. It is designed to provide all essential tools for beginners without including a frame. Buyers are advised to purchase yarn and latex glue separately. Like the ultimate kit, it focuses on simplicity and completeness, making the first steps into tufting straightforward and accessible.</p>
<p>&nbsp;For those seeking a more budget-friendly option, the Basic Tufting Starter Kit is available for €259.00. This kit includes the AK-V tufting machine, 200x200 cm of primary tufting cloth, duckbill napping shears, sewing machine oil, and a loop threader. It is ideal for individuals who plan to build their own frame or prefer a lower initial investment. Customers need to obtain a frame, yarn, and latex carpet glue independently. The AK-V machine included in this kit offers smooth and precise tufting, is lightweight at 1.4 kg, and supports both cut and loop pile styles.</p>
<p>&nbsp;The store also supplies essential tufting cloths. The primary tufting cloth is available in multiple sizes, including 100x100 cm for €7.00, 200x200 cm for €20.00, 300x300 cm for €45.00, and 400x400 cm for €70.00. An anti-slip rug backing measuring 200x200 cm is available for €18.00. These materials provide a solid foundation and professional finish for rugs and wall hangings.</p>
<p>&nbsp;A wide range of accessories enhances the tufting process. Customers can purchase rug shaving and carving clippers, replacement blades, adjustable shaving guides, click-on shaving guides, yarn winders, self-adhesive tape for rug edges, duckbill napping shears, sewing machine oil, yarn threaders, flexible latex spatulas, heavy-duty rug shearing machines, and compatible guides and scissors for various tufting gun models. These tools are designed to streamline workflow, improve precision, and help achieve clean, professional results.</p>
<p>&nbsp;Tufting frames are also available, including a 90x90 cm tabletop frame for €95.00 that clamps securely to a table. Cloth grippers for DIY frames, measuring 750 cm, are available for €29.00. These frames and grippers ensure that tufting cloth remains tightly stretched and stable during work, providing a reliable base for projects.</p>
<p>&nbsp;The yarn collection consists of premium 100 percent New Zealand wool, offered in 500 g cones priced at €17.50 each. The range includes 52 colors across all color families, from neutral tones such as white, black, grey, beige, and brown to vibrant shades of red, orange, yellow, purple, pink, blue, and green. This extensive palette allows artists to create detailed and long-lasting rugs and art pieces with soft, durable wool.</p>
<p>&nbsp;Tufting Europe operates from its headquarters at Johan Van Hasseltweg 12B, 1022WV Amsterdam, and provides contact support via email. The company maintains its commitment to making tufting accessible by delivering high-quality products, fast shipping, and reliable customer service, supporting both beginners and experienced rug makers in bringing their creative visions to life.</p>
